					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is an decent skip, but ultimately I think I’m going to novote. There’s a few interesting ideas but I feel like I’ve seen most of this before, particularily the “person becomes a part of fiction after x event” bit. That said, the way it’s presented looks very nice and the clinical tone is pretty good too. Good Job!</p> <p>Edit: Looking at the article some more, I think I’m going to upvote anyway as it is different enough from the other instances of the “person becomes fiction” thing.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
